DRAM cell stores single bit . It consist of source capacitor and  gate. Capacitors are electric storage. When gate is opened and we have charge source capacitor will get charged . When we close the gate source is blocked and if there is  something in the capacitor it will stay there .
In order to write information to capacitor we open the gate and give voltage to the source and it will be stored inside the capacitor. Gate is door between source and capacitor. Capacitor is battery that holds the charges. There are two kind of lines in cells horizontal lines and vertical lines. Horizontal lines are called word line and vertical lines are called bit line.
In order to read information there we have bit lines . We charge bit lines half of the voltage that is provided for the RAM . We will activate word line and we will open the gates when we open the gates if capacitor is empty it will take a little bit voltage from bitline. When capacitor is full it will release a little bit energy to the bit line.
Since amplifier measures difference between original voltage and the resulting voltage. It is kind of part of the DRAM. If it is less capacity was empty otherwise it was full.
